A 60-year-old woman, Olushola Adebanjo, who allegedly burned her nine-year-old house help with a hot pressing iron, on Tuesday appeared in an Ikeja Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court. Adebanjo, who resides in Agege, Lagos, is charged with assault and reckless conduct. She pleaded not guilty. Prosecution counsel Christopher John told the court that the defendant committed the offence on January 9, at her residence. John said that Adebanjo used a hot pressing iron on the girl for failing to do her chores, adding that she abused the minor whenever she did something wrong. Chief Magistrate P.E. Nwaka admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N100,000 with one surety in like sum, and adjourned the case until March 4.